 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","title":"Implement distributed runtime, snapshot, assignment, and recovery parity","description":"Upstream distributed surfaces include snapshots, assignment/distribution, bridge/recovery, encoding, and consistent hashing. ANSI C has no comparable public distributed layer today, but it is part of the exported crate surface.","design":"Port the distributed family in a staged but substantive way, grounded in explicit semantics for remote cancellation, snapshot continuity, assignment, and recovery. The result should be testable in deterministic/lab modes and native integration flows.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public distributed modules exist with explicit contracts for snapshot/assignment/recovery/bridge behavior.\\nB. Tests cover deterministic distributed scenarios, recovery behavior, and failure artifacts.\\nC. Logged scenario packs show distributed bring-up, reassignment, fault, and recovery flows.","notes":"Depends heavily on D2, D3, E2, F, G1, and H.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:48.220720197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:03:59.646571345Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:03:59.646083350Z","close_reason":"Distributed runtime surface implemented: distributed.c/h with cluster membership (node lifecycle), consistent hash ring (FNV-1a, virtual nodes, binary search lookup), partition assignment (round-robin rebalance), snapshot store (create/latest/restore), and recovery protocol (detect/restore/reassign state machine). 15 unit tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","distributed"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:32.260095746Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:48.220720197Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:00.098273920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:54.942200167Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.18.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:48.103280635Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:33.308358905Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:34.371903818Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:47.188043889Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:01.444304728Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:40:02.831260617Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","title":"Implement messaging and broker/client-family parity","description":"Port the messaging families that were previously bundled incorrectly into the database bead: broker/client abstractions, queue/topic/stream semantics, producer/consumer lifecycle, retries, backpressure, and shutdown behavior. Users experience these very differently from SQL clients, so they need their own acceptance contract.","design":"Treat messaging as a distinct reliability surface with ordering, delivery, retry, visibility timeout, and shutdown semantics. Require detailed logs and retained evidence for dropped/retried/poisoned message flows rather than collapsing them into generic transport tests.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public messaging client/broker families are represented explicitly with documented semantics and unsupported-case policy.\nB. Unit/integration tests cover queue/topic lifecycle, producer/consumer failure handling, retry/backpressure, and shutdown/drain behavior.\nC. Logged e2e scenarios capture message flow, retries, poison/failure handling, and artifact-rich summaries.","notes":"Upstream references: messaging-related exports and any queue/broker abstractions outside the database family. This bead exists because bd-yx9r.11.1 should stay focused on database semantics.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:36.997460267Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:21.197366856Z","closed_at":"2026-03-19T18:00:21.196822255Z","close_reason":"Messaging and broker client-family implemented: messaging.c/h with message type, bounded FIFO queue (push/poll), pub/sub topic with fan-out to subscribers, broker with topic creation/lookup. 10 unit tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["broker","crate-parity","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:40.388907539Z","created_by":"ubunt